    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-24T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-24T09:00:00-05:00" n="736"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d736">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1082a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-24T10:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4714. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 149. Following is for <persName>Alfred Smith</persName> now due Paris on way
                    to Spain: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Bunkering arrangement expires June 25 as agreed, and we would suggest
                            that if you recommend extending date, we stipulate we will license
                            bunkers freely only from United States Atlantic and Gulf ports, reasons
                            for this being that we might desire to control boats going from Cuba to
                            Mexico or passing through the Canal. We would like your opinion promptly
                            as there is shortly due at the Panama Canal the Spanish boat <hi
                                rend="italic">Aviles</hi> with cargo of nitrate for Spain.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
